# Push and Deploy

When the user asks to **push** (or when you push changes to `main` on their behalf):

1. Run tests if code changed (`npm test`).
2. Commit if needed (only when explicitly requested).
3. `git push origin main`
4. **Always run `npm run deploy` immediately after a successful push** unless the user explicitly says not to deploy.

After deploy, confirm:
- Commit hash pushed
- Test result (if run)
- Build/deploy result
- Live URL: https://rawji.github.io/hvac-tech-vision-lab/

Do not skip deploy after push. A GitHub Actions workflow also deploys on push to `main`; local `npm run deploy` keeps Pages in sync immediately without waiting for CI.
